6774cfea-bc54-4743-8edf-beced10f0f6d.459701af-2ea5-4965-bd34-411f6fc0d992.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

6774cfea-bc54-4743-8edf-beced10f0f6d.description=
Synopsis

    This flow builds the NAS configuration for the storage product.
    doPlumbNas performs the following steps\:
      1. Set the failover group name based on the vLan ID.
      2. Check for a node input.
      3. If a node does not exist, use the flow getNodeOfVserver to retrieve the node.
      4. If a node does exist, check for a parent interface input.
      5. If the parent interface does not exist, use the flow getNumNetLifsPerPhysPortLi to retrieve the parentInterface.
      6. If the parent interface does exist, retrieve a list of vLans.
      7. Sort the list of vLans by vLan ID. If none exist on the cluster, check that the LIF exists.
      8. If vLans exist on the cluster, put the list in a xslt format, set a flag to skip the vLan create step, and check that the LIF exists.
      9. If the LIF does exist, determine whether the vLan should be created.
    10. If the LIF does not exist, retrieve a list of LIFs, put the list in a xslt format, set the flag to skip the LIF create step, and decide if the vLan should be created.
    11. Create the vLan (if applicable).
    12. Decide whether to create the LIF.
    13. Generate the LIF interface name.
    14. Create the net interface.
    15. Build the NAS net port configuration, using the flow buildSusNasFgNetPortConfig.
    16. Modify the net interface.
    17. Decide whether to configure the default gateway. Set the default gateway by IP address if configuring.
    18. Reverse the net interface.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer to be used in the flow (required).
    protocol - The protocol used in the flow (i.e. NFS, CIFS, etc) (required).
    ipAddress - The IP address of the LIF (required).
    netMask - The net mask of the IP address (required).
    vlanId - The name of the vLan used in the flow (required).
    failoverGroup - The failover group assigned to the cluster (required).
    node - The contoller node for the clusterName (optional override).
    parentInterface - (optional override). 
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: 

    port - The actual port that the LIF is assigned to (optional override).
    interfaceName -

      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: 

    doLifCheck -

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results
